1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:01,810
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,810 --> 00:00:03,580
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,580 --> 00:00:05,240
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:14,650 --> 00:00:17,560
Dad!

5
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:19,460
I'm not the one
who deserves the blame.

6
00:00:20,230 --> 00:00:21,660
It's Chairman Park Tae Ho!

7
00:00:30,070 --> 00:00:31,200
Adele isn't a good choice.

8
00:00:31,840 --> 00:00:34,770
Don't think about working there,
even as a jewelry designer.

9
00:00:35,510 --> 00:00:36,980
It may be a famous corporation,

10
00:00:37,380 --> 00:00:39,310
but it's not for you, Jin Ju.

11
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:42,110
It could be...

12
00:00:42,680 --> 00:00:43,920
more dangerous than you think.

13
00:00:49,590 --> 00:00:53,490
Min Jun's father is
Chairman Park Tae Ho of Adele Group.

14
00:00:54,660 --> 00:00:57,000
What? Adele Group?

15
00:00:57,900 --> 00:00:59,100
He's the son
of Adele Group's chairman?

16
00:01:01,230 --> 00:01:04,840
Adele Group was targeting
Dad's company.

17
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,840
That's why Dad was so wary
of Adele Group.

18
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:11,110
Chairman Park Tae Ho...

19
00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,080
and Yu Na's father went after Dad,

20
00:01:14,710 --> 00:01:15,950
and Yu Na came after me.

21
00:01:18,020 --> 00:01:20,850
So what am I supposed to do now?

22
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:26,560
He's like a wall.

23
00:01:27,130 --> 00:01:29,430
He's someone
no one in my family can defy.

24
00:01:30,400 --> 00:01:32,600
He's like an insurmountable wall.

25
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,700
That's the kind of man my father is.

26
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:41,610
Min Jun.

27
00:02:20,650 --> 00:02:21,650
James.

28
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:25,780
My dad...

29
00:02:27,250 --> 00:02:28,350
passed away.

30
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,870
(Episode 12)

31
00:02:46,640 --> 00:02:47,640
Where's the chairman?

32
00:02:48,270 --> 00:02:49,740
He went to a breakfast meeting.

33
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,180
Did he?

34
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:54,550
Then I guess breakfast is
all about me today, isn't it?

35
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:57,520
Go on, then. Fill the table
with all of my favorites.

36
00:03:03,660 --> 00:03:05,590
This kimchi turned out so well.

37
00:03:05,820 --> 00:03:07,890
It's fermented just right.
Exactly how I like it.

38
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:14,400
Maybe it's because I've moved
into the main house.

39
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,300
I'm sleeping well,

40
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:19,240
and my appetite has been great
since this morning.

41
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:22,870
Unlike someone here, who looks like
she just bit into a lemon.

42
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:30,550
Delicious.

43
00:03:34,220 --> 00:03:36,520
Until Hyun Jun becomes
the head of Adele Group,

44
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,260
there's nothing I won't do
to stay...

45
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:41,230
on Chairman Park's good side.

46
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:45,260
No matter how many die,
we push forward.

47
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:46,630
Got it?

48
00:03:54,740 --> 00:03:55,810
Aren't you going to eat?

49
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,720
What do you think you're doing?

50
00:04:09,350 --> 00:04:11,360
What if Oh Jung Ran
or someone else in the family sees you?

51
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,190
I just can't stand it anymore.

52
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:15,760
Someone died so unfairly,

53
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:17,860
and she can't just walk around
like nothing happened.

54
00:04:20,200 --> 00:04:22,230
When my sister died,
there was no evidence.

55
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:25,570
But this time, if I find evidence,
I can press charges.

56
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,940
I'll find a ledger proving
Oh Jung Ran created a slush fund...

57
00:04:31,010 --> 00:04:32,540
and used it for lobbying,

58
00:04:33,410 --> 00:04:34,910
or I'll find her reports
to the chairman,

59
00:04:34,910 --> 00:04:36,010
and take it all to the police.

60
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:37,480
What?

61
00:04:39,380 --> 00:04:40,390
Dan Hui.

62
00:04:46,990 --> 00:04:47,990
All this time,

63
00:04:49,630 --> 00:04:52,100
I've gritted my teeth
and endured it,

64
00:04:53,970 --> 00:04:56,870
but I'm just as powerless now
as I was back then.

65
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:04,040
I feel so pathetic
for being so weak and foolish.

66
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:08,380
Even more than that monster,
Oh Jung Ran,

67
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:11,180
I can't stand...

68
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:14,120
how useless I am.

69
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,160
But you've been protecting Min Jun
all this time.

70
00:05:20,860 --> 00:05:23,130
And you'll keep protecting him, right?

71
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:30,640
For now, focus on taking Adele Group
from Oh Jung Ran.

72
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,200
That's all you should think about.

73
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:35,270
Take what Oh Jung Ran wants most,

74
00:05:35,270 --> 00:05:36,970
get justice for your sister,

75
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:39,480
and become stronger
than Oh Jung Ran.

76
00:05:39,480 --> 00:05:41,550
That's how you'll protect Min Jun.

77
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:45,150
Only with power...

78
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:47,590
can you get justice
for what happened to Dr. Baek.

79
00:05:48,520 --> 00:05:50,490
You know that, don't you?

80
00:06:20,250 --> 00:06:22,620
Yu Na, why do you look like that?

81
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:25,260
Are you not feeling well?

82
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:28,460
Dad, are you okay?

83
00:06:28,630 --> 00:06:29,630
What?

84
00:06:29,690 --> 00:06:31,600
What do you mean?

85
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:33,770
CEO Baek...

86
00:06:35,530 --> 00:06:38,740
Good grief.
You must be sad that she died,

87
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:41,170
since she was your friend after all.

88
00:06:41,170 --> 00:06:42,310
Goodness,

89
00:06:42,370 --> 00:06:46,040
when she was still alive,
you hated her guts.

90
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:50,450
Are you getting all sentimental
now that she's gone?

91
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:55,320
I suppose it's true what they say
about the future being unknown.

92
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:59,160
Who would've thought this would
be how the Baeks ended up?

93
00:06:59,990 --> 00:07:03,460
Still, life goes on
for those of us who remain.

94
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:07,200
Thanks to CEO Baek's death,

95
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:10,130
your dad got to sell the company
and acquire stock.

96
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:12,300
He made a killing.

97
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:16,810
And you!
You won that design competition,

98
00:07:16,870 --> 00:07:18,910
so now you get to study abroad.

99
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:20,380
The competition?

100
00:07:21,180 --> 00:07:22,310
That's right!

101
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:25,150
Adele called and said
you should come pick up your award.

102
00:07:25,250 --> 00:07:29,150
Goodness,
why didn't you tell us sooner?

103
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:33,120
I could've gotten a new outfit
for the occasion.

104
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:34,890
Why would you need more...

105
00:07:34,890 --> 00:07:36,960
when your closet is packed
with clothes?

106
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:40,900
It's full of clothes I can't wear
to an awards ceremony.

107
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:43,840
Whatever.
I have to find something to wear...

108
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:46,840
and do my hair,
so everyone get ready.

109
00:07:47,040 --> 00:07:49,970
And stop moping around
over the dead.

110
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:51,540
She's right.

111
00:07:51,540 --> 00:07:54,280
The dead are gone,

112
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:56,450
but we still have to keep living.

113
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:59,480
Exactly. You two weren't that close,

114
00:07:59,550 --> 00:08:00,950
so stop moping around.

115
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:02,550
Hurry up and get ready.

116
00:08:02,620 --> 00:08:04,960
We don't have all day. Come on.

117
00:08:14,270 --> 00:08:15,500
The dead...

118
00:08:16,170 --> 00:08:17,340
are gone.

119
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,040
If there's really no going back now,

120
00:08:23,170 --> 00:08:24,680
am I supposed to just enjoy...

121
00:08:25,210 --> 00:08:26,510
what I've taken?

122
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:33,990
(The Nation's Police
Built on Strong Fundamentals)

123
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,890
(Return of Personal Effects,
Baek Jun Gi Car Explosion Case)

124
00:08:41,930 --> 00:08:44,930
The watch you found at the accident scene
and turned in...

125
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,430
has been determined
not to be related to the case.

126
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:49,930
Since no legal next of kin
could be identified,

127
00:08:49,930 --> 00:08:52,870
we've been approved to return it
to the person who submitted it.

128
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,440
Hyun Jun.

129
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:32,110
Hey, what are you doing out here?

130
00:09:34,050 --> 00:09:36,150
I was just thinking.

131
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:39,650
What were you thinking,
looking so sad?

132
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:41,990
Do I look...

133
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:44,520
sad right now?

134
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:46,860
Yes, that's exactly
how I used to look.

135
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:48,860
Well...

136
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:51,630
It looks like you have
a one-sided crush.

137
00:09:58,500 --> 00:09:59,640
Don't tell me it's true.

138
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:01,140
Is that...

139
00:10:02,570 --> 00:10:04,040
what's going on?

140
00:10:04,210 --> 00:10:06,740
Is there really someone you like?

141
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:10,310
Someone I like?

142
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:13,820
It's complicated.

143
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,120
Complicated?

144
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:17,620
What's so complicated?

145
00:10:17,920 --> 00:10:19,520
Is it the relationship
that's complicated,

146
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:21,160
or your feelings?

147
00:10:21,260 --> 00:10:24,260
Or is she just kind of so-so?

148
00:10:24,930 --> 00:10:27,400
What good would talking about it do?

149
00:10:28,370 --> 00:10:30,170
You're not exactly a romance expert.

150
00:10:30,700 --> 00:10:33,900
We can be experts
on other people's love lives,

151
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:35,110
even if our own is a mess.

152
00:10:35,210 --> 00:10:37,610
First, tell me what's on your mind,
and I'll...

153
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:39,080
If I tell you,

154
00:10:39,380 --> 00:10:41,650
you'll just run and tell Ms. Oh.

155
00:10:41,810 --> 00:10:43,950
No, I wouldn't.

156
00:10:43,950 --> 00:10:45,920
If so, then just drop it.

157
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,690
Fine, all right.

158
00:10:47,690 --> 00:10:49,090
I'll play dumb,

159
00:10:49,150 --> 00:10:51,190
- so just tell me...
- Just drop it, please.

160
00:10:51,260 --> 00:10:53,060
- Come on. I'll keep it to myself.
- Head on in.

161
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,590
Hyun Jun, what's on your mind?

162
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:56,130
- Hyun Jun!
- Just go away.

163
00:10:57,360 --> 00:11:00,700
Hyun Jun, what's on your mind?
Tell me!

164
00:11:01,670 --> 00:11:03,030
Unbelievable.

165
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,490
Here's another thing I thought.

166
00:11:31,930 --> 00:11:33,830
Are these memories...

167
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,540
the only things I'm allowed to have?

168
00:11:40,910 --> 00:11:42,170
I actually thought that.

169
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:57,250
We promised
we'd be together forever.

170
00:12:05,630 --> 00:12:07,800
Will being together like this...

171
00:12:08,970 --> 00:12:10,530
be enough for me?

172
00:12:23,050 --> 00:12:25,120
(University College of Business
and Management Birmingham)

173
00:12:49,710 --> 00:12:50,710
The Grand Prize...

174
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:52,880
for the Adele Group
Design Competition...

175
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,040
goes to Choi Yu Na.

176
00:12:58,350 --> 00:12:59,350
Park Tae Ho.

177
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:03,750
You, of all people,
must know Oh Jung Ran's crimes.

178
00:13:04,590 --> 00:13:06,660
You know everything,
yet you pretend not to.

179
00:13:07,090 --> 00:13:09,760
You steal Dr. Baek's company
and think that's the end of it?

180
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:13,530
You, them,

181
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,630
and even me.

182
00:13:16,470 --> 00:13:18,470
Is everyone just looking out
for themselves?

183
00:13:20,870 --> 00:13:21,870
Here.

184
00:13:23,540 --> 00:13:24,710
How does it feel...

185
00:13:24,710 --> 00:13:26,540
to win the top prize
in the design competition?

186
00:13:27,110 --> 00:13:28,110
Sorry?

187
00:13:29,550 --> 00:13:31,820
Oh, right. Well...

188
00:13:32,150 --> 00:13:33,920
Don't get distracted.

189
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:36,320
Just focus on your studies abroad.

190
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:40,960
Now that you have your wings,
you must fly to the very top.

191
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,170
Gosh, sir. No way.

192
00:13:49,470 --> 00:13:51,100
She still has a long way to go.

193
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:52,740
The top is probably
out of reach for now.

194
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,170
Now, if it were Jin Ju...

195
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:05,550
Honey, why are you comparing
our Yu Na to someone who's dead?

196
00:14:05,620 --> 00:14:09,120
To be honest, if our Yu Na
really sets her mind to it,

197
00:14:09,190 --> 00:14:11,360
there's nothing she can't achieve.

198
00:14:13,690 --> 00:14:15,960
Yes, that's right.

199
00:14:16,430 --> 00:14:19,430
Just as you said, Chairman Park,

200
00:14:20,200 --> 00:14:23,200
I'm going to fly to the very top.

201
00:14:27,470 --> 00:14:28,470
That's right.

202
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:31,440
I'll make what I took from Jin Ju...

203
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:33,740
mine.

204
00:14:42,890 --> 00:14:43,890
Mother.

205
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:53,000
Why, of all people,

206
00:14:53,560 --> 00:14:55,330
did it have to be her
and my Min Jun?

207
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:13,680
It won't be easy.

208
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:18,090
- Sorry?
- A goal like reaching the top...

209
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:20,190
never really ends.

210
00:15:21,530 --> 00:15:24,090
A little more. Just a little more.

211
00:15:24,730 --> 00:15:26,060
As your greed grows,

212
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,800
it can consume you...

213
00:15:29,430 --> 00:15:30,970
and turn you into a monster.

214
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:37,540
What was that? A monster?

215
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:41,910
Of course.
We wouldn't want that to happen.

216
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:46,550
Take this as my encouragement,
and remember it well.

217
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:12,140
Goodness, what is with her?

218
00:16:17,380 --> 00:16:18,550
Good grief.

219
00:16:25,290 --> 00:16:26,590
Excuse me. Just a moment.

220
00:16:35,730 --> 00:16:37,770
I don't think
becoming a monster is a bad thing.

221
00:16:39,170 --> 00:16:41,510
Unless you want to struggle
at the bottom,

222
00:16:42,210 --> 00:16:44,340
you have to be a monster
so people...

223
00:16:44,910 --> 00:16:47,240
don't take what's yours
and walk all over you.

224
00:16:47,780 --> 00:16:48,780
Am I wrong?

225
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,050
Is she right?

226
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,520
Is that really
the right way to live?

227
00:16:55,590 --> 00:16:57,290
Instead of being crushed
and losing everything,

228
00:16:57,290 --> 00:16:58,390
only to regret it later,

229
00:16:59,490 --> 00:17:02,230
I'd rather be ready
to become a monster.

230
00:17:05,060 --> 00:17:06,160
Just you watch.

231
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:08,000
When I come back,

232
00:17:09,130 --> 00:17:10,900
you'll have no choice
but to acknowledge me.

233
00:17:27,380 --> 00:17:29,090
Being ready to become a monster?

234
00:17:35,760 --> 00:17:37,730
(Public Health Center)

235
00:17:51,740 --> 00:17:52,980
James.

236
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:56,580
- Oh, Jin Ju.
- James.

237
00:17:57,850 --> 00:17:59,050
Goodness me.

238
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:02,490
Thank you so much.

239
00:18:02,990 --> 00:18:06,460
- Thank you for being alive.
- James.

240
00:18:08,360 --> 00:18:09,690
My dad...

241
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,370
I know. I know everything.

242
00:18:16,070 --> 00:18:18,270
- I know it all.
- James.

243
00:18:19,170 --> 00:18:21,100
I left my dad all alone,

244
00:18:21,810 --> 00:18:23,310
and I'm the only one who...

245
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:26,110
Just by myself...

246
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,190
Mr. Baek...

247
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,560
would've been relieved to know
that you survived.

248
00:18:41,660 --> 00:18:43,630
He'd say it was a blessing
a thousand times over.

249
00:18:45,630 --> 00:18:49,570
He's still watching over you
from up there.

250
00:18:58,980 --> 00:19:00,440
It'll be okay.

251
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:21,730
(The late Baek Jun Gi,
The late Baek Jin Ju)

252
00:19:23,330 --> 00:19:25,240
This was the best I could do
on short notice.

253
00:19:27,140 --> 00:19:29,740
They found your watch
at the accident scene,

254
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:31,740
and since you have no next of kin,

255
00:19:32,080 --> 00:19:35,480
they gave it to the finder,
a guy named Park Min Jun.

256
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:37,110
Min Jun...

257
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:41,990
Have you looked into it?

258
00:19:43,890 --> 00:19:46,790
Was it really Yu Na's family...

259
00:19:48,930 --> 00:19:50,990
and Park Tae Ho,
the chairman of Adele Group,

260
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,560
who did this to my dad?

261
00:19:54,330 --> 00:19:56,430
Yes, it seems that way.

262
00:19:57,570 --> 00:19:59,040
All the evidence points to it.

263
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:02,540
So there's no use
going to the police?

264
00:20:03,610 --> 00:20:06,540
They had the means and ruthlessness
to frame Mr. Baek as a criminal...

265
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:09,450
and stage his death
to look like a suicide.

266
00:20:09,450 --> 00:20:11,820
I'm certain
the cover-up was airtight.

267
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:13,720
Even if there is evidence,

268
00:20:14,350 --> 00:20:15,950
they've probably hidden it well.

269
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:18,560
If you go to the police
without proof,

270
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:20,990
they might come after you again.

271
00:20:22,890 --> 00:20:24,360
Then there's nothing...

272
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,270
I can do...

273
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,270
for my dad?

274
00:20:35,870 --> 00:20:37,240
As infuriating and unfair as it is,

275
00:20:37,870 --> 00:20:39,340
there's nothing we can do right now.

276
00:20:41,410 --> 00:20:44,350
The car explosion was so intense
that they couldn't identify anyone.

277
00:20:45,320 --> 00:20:48,550
It's a miracle
that no one knows you survived.

278
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:59,060
My dad...

279
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:01,300
saved my life.

280
00:21:02,400 --> 00:21:03,770
My dad...

281
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:08,610
He protected me until the very end.

282
00:21:11,110 --> 00:21:13,180
And yet, I can't do anything...

283
00:21:16,080 --> 00:21:17,980
I can't do a single thing for him.

284
00:21:28,490 --> 00:21:29,490
Dad.

285
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,800
Dad...

286
00:21:33,860 --> 00:21:37,270
(The late Baek Jun Gi,
The late Baek Jin Ju)

287
00:21:37,330 --> 00:21:39,400
Dad!

288
00:21:44,010 --> 00:21:45,940
I'm sorry, Dad.

289
00:21:48,410 --> 00:21:49,880
I'm so sorry!

290
00:21:52,620 --> 00:21:55,290
I couldn't even save you,

291
00:21:55,990 --> 00:21:58,360
and I'm the only one
who made it out alive.

292
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:02,230
You were unjustly murdered!

293
00:22:04,390 --> 00:22:07,230
They dragged your name
through the mud!

294
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:12,300
But all I can do is hide like this.

295
00:22:13,370 --> 00:22:17,510
There's nothing I can do for you.

296
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,240
I'm sorry.

297
00:22:23,610 --> 00:22:25,720
I'm sorry, Dad.

298
00:22:26,420 --> 00:22:28,150
Dad.

299
00:22:29,850 --> 00:22:31,350
Dad.

300
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:36,060
Dad...

301
00:23:42,390 --> 00:23:44,330
What do you think you're doing?

302
00:23:45,460 --> 00:23:47,300
As if you don't know.

303
00:23:47,830 --> 00:23:50,870
Hey, now. Don't start that.

304
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:52,970
Stop it.

305
00:23:53,340 --> 00:23:56,410
Don't touch me. Get away from me!

306
00:24:25,370 --> 00:24:27,800
I need to speak with you
for a moment.

307
00:24:29,240 --> 00:24:31,940
You do? Come in.

308
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,750
You, get out of the way. Come on in.

309
00:24:40,120 --> 00:24:42,550
If you have something to say,
say it here or in the study.

310
00:24:42,950 --> 00:24:45,090
Why are you taking that tramp
into our bedroom?

311
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:49,060
You think this is your bedroom?
It's clearly mine.

312
00:24:49,130 --> 00:24:51,360
If you don't like it,
you can move out to the annex.

313
00:24:51,660 --> 00:24:53,600
- Get out of my way.
- No.

314
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:54,900
Move!

315
00:24:55,970 --> 00:24:57,200
Come on in.

316
00:25:03,540 --> 00:25:05,040
You!

317
00:25:07,340 --> 00:25:09,650
Darn it!

318
00:25:10,750 --> 00:25:12,080
(Temi Bio Project,
Research Proposal Guide)

319
00:25:13,550 --> 00:25:14,750
Please approve my request.

320
00:25:14,750 --> 00:25:16,950
If you find
this business plan acceptable,

321
00:25:17,090 --> 00:25:18,890
I'd like to be put in charge
of Temi Bio,

322
00:25:19,220 --> 00:25:20,760
which you recently acquired.

323
00:25:23,090 --> 00:25:25,000
If you put me in charge of Temi Bio,

324
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,000
I'll handle the dirty work...

325
00:25:28,700 --> 00:25:30,500
like your wife does.

326
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:48,890
(The late Baek Jun Gi,
The late Baek Jin Ju)

327
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:50,790
In that case...

328
00:25:51,290 --> 00:25:52,460
Why don't you come with me?

329
00:25:53,090 --> 00:25:55,560
We agreed to meet
at the courier company.

330
00:25:56,060 --> 00:25:57,060
All right.

331
00:25:57,590 --> 00:26:00,200
I'm sure Jin Ju will cool down
and call you soon.

332
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:04,530
(The late Baek Jun Gi,
The late Baek Jin Ju)

333
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:08,270
Was this your plan all along?

334
00:26:09,610 --> 00:26:11,170
I tried to tell myself
it wasn't true.

335
00:26:11,170 --> 00:26:12,710
That it couldn't be.

336
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:14,980
But with all the evidence
that's surfaced,

337
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:18,980
everyone is saying the same thing.

338
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:24,120
That you hurt the innocent Jin Ju...

339
00:26:30,630 --> 00:26:32,260
People are so cruel.

340
00:26:34,660 --> 00:26:36,930
Your father took your life
like it was his right,

341
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:40,070
and they buried you here with him...

342
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:45,140
just because you're his daughter.

343
00:26:47,810 --> 00:26:50,480
I wish I'd proposed
the moment I met you...

344
00:26:52,520 --> 00:26:54,080
and fell in love.

345
00:26:54,150 --> 00:26:55,390
(The late Baek Jun Gi,
The late Baek Jin Ju)

346
00:26:58,420 --> 00:26:59,560
If we had been family,

347
00:27:01,220 --> 00:27:02,530
and if I'd been there
to protect you,

348
00:27:06,430 --> 00:27:08,370
I never would've let
this happen to you.

349
00:27:11,330 --> 00:27:12,340
I...

350
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:16,940
will never forgive the man
who killed you.

351
00:27:18,510 --> 00:27:21,810
I know you'd say it's okay,
that you forgave him.

352
00:27:23,980 --> 00:27:25,380
But every time I visit your grave,

353
00:27:25,380 --> 00:27:27,980
I will hate him
with every fiber of my being.

354
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:29,750
(The late Baek Jun Gi,
The late Baek Jin Ju)

355
00:27:29,750 --> 00:27:31,450
Coming here to see you...

356
00:27:33,760 --> 00:27:35,590
and missing you like this...

357
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,230
has already become unbearable.

358
00:27:42,700 --> 00:27:44,570
Will I be able to keep living,

359
00:27:45,840 --> 00:27:47,300
leaving you here like this?

360
00:27:51,210 --> 00:27:53,410
How can I possibly live...

361
00:27:54,610 --> 00:27:55,680
in a world...

362
00:27:57,050 --> 00:27:58,280
without you?

363
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:00,880
Won't you regret this?

364
00:29:02,150 --> 00:29:03,350
If you leave like this,

365
00:29:04,410 --> 00:29:06,080
everyone will think you're dead.

366
00:29:06,750 --> 00:29:09,890
I'm already living
with so many regrets.

367
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:15,020
Are you sure you can
just leave him like that?

368
00:29:15,930 --> 00:29:17,860
He thinks he lost
the most precious person in his life,

369
00:29:19,230 --> 00:29:20,730
and he'll be in so much pain.

370
00:29:26,870 --> 00:29:27,870
I...

371
00:29:29,570 --> 00:29:31,140
lost my father.

372
00:29:33,510 --> 00:29:34,940
In those flames,

373
00:29:37,010 --> 00:29:40,520
everything I had burned away.

374
00:29:44,020 --> 00:29:45,360
All I have left now...

375
00:29:46,990 --> 00:29:49,860
is revenge.

376
00:29:52,330 --> 00:29:53,530
And my revenge begins...

377
00:29:54,860 --> 00:29:56,730
by killing the person I used to be.

378
00:30:11,950 --> 00:30:12,950
Okay.

379
00:30:29,930 --> 00:30:32,100
(Adele)

380
00:30:32,170 --> 00:30:35,470
(Year 2026)

381
00:30:37,370 --> 00:30:39,680
(Choi Yu Na,
Head of New Business Task Force)

382
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:04,930
Good morning, Director Kim.

383
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:07,440
Sure.

384
00:32:10,170 --> 00:32:13,100
(Pearl in Red)

385
00:32:13,470 --> 00:32:15,840
Does the name Baek Jin Ju
bother you?

386
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:16,840
Excuse me?

387
00:32:16,840 --> 00:32:18,210
So who exactly is Baek Jin Ju?

388
00:32:18,340 --> 00:32:22,850
This family has a wedding coming up,
yet no one is smiling.

389
00:32:23,580 --> 00:32:25,420
If you're going to do this,
then do it right.

390
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:29,050
I'm the one you need,
not the ghost of Baek Jin Ju.

391
00:32:29,250 --> 00:32:32,160
You stole her designs
and her dreams,

392
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:34,090
and now
you're stealing her marriage.

393
00:32:34,160 --> 00:32:35,730
So leave it at that.

394
00:32:35,730 --> 00:32:37,890
Don't get greedy
and think you can have me too.

395
00:32:38,360 --> 00:32:40,360
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
